WEBVTT

00:04.162 --> 00:30.002
Colossians chapter 4 beginning verse 2 continue earnestly in prayer Being vigilant in it with Thanksgiving Meanwhile praying also for us The God would open to us a door for the word To speak the mystery of Christ for which I am also in chains

00:31.330 --> 00:34.433
that I may make it manifest as I ought to speak.

00:35.775 --> 00:40.600
Walk in wisdom toward those who are outside, redeeming the time.

00:41.601 --> 00:44.505
Let your speech always be with grace.

00:45.586 --> 00:51.232
Season with salt that you may know how you want to answer each one.

00:52.193 --> 00:53.915
This is the Word of God for the people of God.

00:56.418 --> 00:56.718
Amen.

00:56.738 --> 00:59.181
May God add his blessing to the reading of his words.

00:59.201 --> 01:00.082
You may be seated.

01:15.426 --> 01:19.312
I call this one roots and routes.

01:19.332 --> 01:25.000
Sometimes we say like root 66 or route 66.

01:25.421 --> 01:26.382
Each one is correct.

01:27.224 --> 01:30.428
But the word root in roots and routes is like a tree root.

01:30.829 --> 01:33.553
And the word route could also be pronounced roots.

01:33.833 --> 01:35.296
So it could be called roots and roots.

01:37.138 --> 01:39.261
Or roots and routes, however you want to call it.

01:40.223 --> 01:42.386
But I'm going to use the word route

01:43.010 --> 01:51.684
And sometimes I'm going to tell you this is a root thing, but the root thing is going to be the roots that dig deep, not the road.

01:54.628 --> 02:08.250
I want to talk about community today because it's important to know what that's all about and understand when we're looking at community, how to approach it, what we're thinking about to have the same mindset.

02:09.953 --> 02:10.834
And the verse that

02:10.946 --> 02:39.026
draws my attention to Community is Jeremiah chapter 29 verse 7 This is a period of time in Israel's history where they're in captivity They've been taken into Babylon and God gives them this word it says seek the peace and prosperity of the city where I have sent you pray to the Lord for it and

02:39.362 --> 02:42.546
For in its peace, you will have peace.

02:44.989 --> 02:52.058
Now, I'm going to just unpack that verse a little bit so you understand the dynamic of what's going on.

02:52.919 --> 02:56.323
Israel was overtaken by Babylon.

02:57.524 --> 03:00.508
They took all the things out of the temple.

03:00.849 --> 03:04.854
They took most of the Jewish people out and back to Babylon.

03:05.675 --> 03:08.498
And God had told them if they didn't get their act straight,

03:08.578 --> 03:10.059
This was going to happen.

03:11.901 --> 03:14.504
They didn't get their act straight and it happened.

03:16.046 --> 03:29.960
Now, if they were ever going to be in captivity and you look at the story of the Babylonian captivity, you will see that that captivity is actually not a bad one.

03:30.981 --> 03:34.885
They weren't turned into slaves and taskmasters like some would have.

03:35.325 --> 03:36.306
They actually were allowed

03:36.450 --> 03:38.853
to do some things and have some of their own freedoms.

03:39.874 --> 03:48.203
But what God says in this verse is seek the prosperity of the city where I sent you and it's peace.

03:50.626 --> 04:01.979
And God's saying where I sent you, sometimes we go to a place where we don't want to be and God calls us to a place we don't want to go.

04:02.840 --> 04:05.042
Sometimes it's because we need to be there

04:05.186 --> 04:07.309
Sometimes because we had to be there.

04:09.492 --> 04:18.045
The Israelites went because they had to be there, because they're disobedience.

04:18.065 --> 04:25.496
And so he says, when that happens, no matter where you find yourself, pray for the peace of the place you're at.

04:27.579 --> 04:34.930
Because if that place has prosperity and peace, you will get some of that as well.

04:36.066 --> 04:51.103
So if they're in good fortune, they're not going to be so much worried about whether or not you have good fortune or are not having good fortune because they're going to bless you with their abundance.

04:51.123 --> 04:52.425
And that's why he said that.

04:56.029 --> 05:03.698
And so what happened in this time in their history was when they took into captivity, they left their homeland.

05:04.450 --> 05:08.595
They were transported to another area and this is what they said.

05:09.196 --> 05:10.797
This is your new community.

05:11.759 --> 05:12.940
This is your home.

05:13.941 --> 05:17.926
And for 70 years, it was 70.

05:18.747 --> 05:25.174
So when you're transporting the captivity, you don't know how long you're going to be at a place or a time.

05:26.295 --> 05:31.922
But wherever you are becomes your community.

05:33.570 --> 05:34.571
Now what is community?

05:35.993 --> 06:01.106
That's a word we need to do a little bit on packing on because if you grew up in the 70s, 80s, 90s and heard the word community it means something different than what I'm saying today because back in the 70s we had a guy named Jim Jones and he had a community in Indiana and he went down to South America

06:01.890 --> 06:03.772
and it moved his community there.

06:04.674 --> 06:05.615
And they made the news.

06:05.675 --> 06:12.564
So when you heard about that being a community and you're going, here's some community living opportunities, you're going, I don't know if I want that.

06:13.405 --> 06:24.199
So when I was experiencing all those different things that were happening in a lot of a cult like stuff, when someone said, community's good, I would say, no, it's not.

06:24.820 --> 06:29.586
I had a very negative impact in my mind of the word community.

06:29.858 --> 06:34.484
So when people would say community, I'd say, well, this is all these people invading my space and I don't need them.

06:36.266 --> 06:37.728
But it was such a buzzword.

06:39.771 --> 06:47.882
And I didn't see it as I do now, which is harmonious together and it's working together to help each other for similar cause.

06:48.563 --> 06:52.408
Right now, in my life and time, I love community.

06:53.850 --> 06:57.074
I'm a part of a large community besides our church.

06:57.666 --> 07:01.051
On Friday night, I'm a part of the Celebrate Recovery Community.

07:01.571 --> 07:05.016
My wife and I have been ministry leaders there since 2009.

07:05.056 --> 07:13.728
A lot of our friends, if not most of them, came from that community or are still in that community.

07:14.610 --> 07:26.386
And they help each other and they understand each other because we know each other's stories, because we've been working on stuff to get healthier, mentally, emotionally, physically.

07:28.162 --> 07:29.103
So imagine this.

07:31.386 --> 07:39.274
I asked my wife when I could work on the kitchen floor and dining room floor, which is with travesty from the guy that installed it.

07:40.976 --> 07:42.738
And she said, why don't you do it while I'm on the cruise?

07:43.539 --> 07:46.542
I won't be around and you'll have plenty of time to do it.

07:48.004 --> 07:52.849
So Friday between school routes, I start working on it.

07:54.431 --> 07:57.234
By the time I had to go back to the routes, I realized

07:57.442 --> 07:59.805
I might not get this done by the time she gets home.

08:02.710 --> 08:07.176
So Friday we had celebrate recovery and I'm talking to some guys there about it.

08:08.037 --> 08:09.760
And one guy says, I'll come over and help you.

08:10.201 --> 08:10.701
And I said, really?

08:10.881 --> 08:12.223
He said, yeah, why not?

08:12.604 --> 08:13.105
I'll help you.

08:14.827 --> 08:16.269
My son also said he would help.

08:16.650 --> 08:25.042
So Saturday morning, about 9.13 in the morning, my son comes in and says, let's start on the floor.

08:25.186 --> 08:37.862
I'd already done 10 rows already after turning it out and putting new rows in and we started working on it and we worked on it and I worked on it until I got ready to come to the retirement party and I went back and I worked on it until about midnight.

08:39.024 --> 08:46.533
My son worked the whole time and my friend came around three after he got off work and stayed until midnight as well.

08:47.595 --> 08:48.676
We didn't quite get it done.

08:49.697 --> 08:53.362
Still had 20 pieces left and my friend says

08:53.986 --> 08:55.208
He's from Silver Recovery.

08:55.248 --> 08:59.554
He said, I'm going to come back tomorrow more than 7.30 and finish this out.

09:00.735 --> 09:04.280
And I said, listen, you got churchy going, no, listen.

09:04.300 --> 09:05.602
My buddy has a need.

09:06.102 --> 09:08.826
You've helped me in so many ways to have a better life.

09:09.307 --> 09:10.288
I want to help you.

09:12.892 --> 09:22.304
So he shows up with his family in tow because they're all together, you know, and he starts working on it.

09:22.945 --> 09:23.506
And I said,

09:23.714 --> 09:26.737
I can't help you saying, oh, don't worry, I got this.

09:27.638 --> 09:33.964
And I'm thinking, by the time I get home from church today, I'll still have some more to finish.

09:35.085 --> 09:36.987
And I'm going, I hope not, but we'll see.

09:38.268 --> 09:45.775
On the way here, he texted me three pictures, everything done in a furniture I'll put back in place.

09:48.338 --> 09:51.100
I am humbly grateful by community.

09:51.761 --> 09:53.042
That's community.

09:53.730 --> 09:55.312
That's, I said, thank you.

09:55.332 --> 09:58.215
He said, no, thank you for what you've done to my life.

09:58.235 --> 10:01.578
And I said, well, I'm humbly grateful that you did this because my body would give out.

10:03.080 --> 10:04.000
And so it's done.

10:04.681 --> 10:12.269
And now I can go out and get ready for Christine to come home and do all the things I need to do to prepare for that and not have that in the back of my head.

10:12.309 --> 10:18.395
And I know that when she comes in, she's going to go, thank you.

10:19.076 --> 10:21.138
She won't know how long that took.

10:22.050 --> 10:27.096
And if there's something wrong with it, I'll say yes, I'll see what I can do, but not today.

10:29.379 --> 10:36.828
So that's what I'm saying by community is when you need help, community there to help you to encourage you to support you.

10:37.149 --> 10:38.470
You all know that.

10:39.812 --> 10:40.873
We have senior dinners.

10:40.913 --> 10:41.714
We get together.

10:42.115 --> 10:43.316
Yes, it's retirement.

10:45.039 --> 10:47.762
I get you call it party celebration dinner.

10:49.154 --> 11:18.770
a lunch and supper as much as was there but what I'm saying is we also when there's a funeral we gather together we we are there for each other that's community there's nothing wrong with the community it's good but the problem is is sometimes we don't trust it and I'll start with saying that if you live isolated you won't feel as much community because you won't let people come to help you

11:19.650 --> 11:28.960
or you be closed off, and communities there to support and encourage you, even when you don't want it, because that's what it does.

11:29.401 --> 11:30.362
That's what love does.

11:32.885 --> 11:45.459
In every community, no matter what kind it is, there are two types of residents, two types of people, if you will, those who live in a place and those who live for it.

11:46.480 --> 11:48.082
A person who lives in a place

11:49.506 --> 11:50.427
They build fences.

11:52.229 --> 11:52.790
I live here.

11:52.850 --> 11:53.771
You live over there.

11:53.811 --> 11:54.652
This is me.

11:54.932 --> 11:56.334
I'm my family.

11:56.374 --> 11:57.155
This is us.

11:57.475 --> 11:58.056
You're over there.

11:58.076 --> 11:58.657
You're different.

11:59.217 --> 12:04.724
But those who not just live in it, but live for it, they plant gardens.

12:06.826 --> 12:12.633
They create community gardens too sometimes and they feed others and share their produce with others.

12:13.374 --> 12:17.298
Pat Rogers Sullivan are kind of like that over there in New Liberty.

12:17.538 --> 12:43.058
He has a whole bunch of produce he grows and he gives it away to anybody who wants it and that's community That's what we're talking about how we bless and love each other because we care because we can Some of us though build walls to live our life in isolation when we do that and

12:44.034 --> 12:48.599
We never make a difference or make an impact on the lives around us.

12:50.802 --> 12:55.447
When God puts you in a place, it's not random.

12:57.289 --> 13:00.833
The people you come across are not coincidental.

13:01.674 --> 13:05.318
God is desiring to use you for his purposes.

13:11.004 --> 13:12.786
We are rooted

13:13.058 --> 13:16.683
like a tree in God's presence.

13:18.105 --> 13:23.833
And he also sends us along the routes where we find out where we have our impactful purpose.

13:25.715 --> 13:29.801
We are not just occupants of our community, we are ambassadors.

13:30.862 --> 13:33.686
In other words, if someone says, what kind of community do you live in man?

13:33.806 --> 13:34.487
You got to know.

13:34.948 --> 13:36.570
What kind of churches you got to know.

13:36.710 --> 13:40.555
And let me tell you, because we're ambassadors for what we love.

13:41.497 --> 13:42.578
What we talk about

13:42.754 --> 13:46.199
is what's heavy on our heart, or strong on our heart.

13:46.219 --> 13:51.426
And when we talk about it, like, man, you just got to know how wonderful these people are in this places.

13:52.668 --> 14:04.665
If you ever look online at people exploring places to live, the number one question they ask is, what is the community like?

14:06.328 --> 14:08.050
What's there to do in that community?

14:08.130 --> 14:10.052
What resources are in the community?

14:10.072 --> 14:16.099
They want to know if they're going to feel like they have a place where they can connect.

14:18.301 --> 14:19.983
Connecting is so important.

14:27.131 --> 14:33.558
You're on YouTube.

14:34.018 --> 14:34.659
That's funny.

14:35.079 --> 14:37.682
Our address where we live

14:38.306 --> 14:40.128
is a part of our assignment.

14:41.370 --> 14:46.237
Some folks I know open their home and love people well.

14:55.909 --> 15:08.306
When God told Israel what was going to happen in Babylon in chapter 29 of Jeremiah, they're already in exile when he says these words.

15:08.578 --> 15:37.490
build houses plant gardens multiply there in other words if you can't get out of it get into it go into it go for it don't make excuses live this like it's your home for now because it is and make an impact on how well you serve me there and so wherever we are planted

15:37.890 --> 15:40.193
God expects fruit.

15:44.758 --> 15:49.224
He also told them to pray the Lord for the city.

15:49.985 --> 16:02.861
Now, if you're in captivity or in bondage to somebody and God says pray for them, that's going to come across as difficult if you're not happy about your situation.

16:03.301 --> 16:07.026
But God doesn't say, well, okay,

16:07.170 --> 16:09.953
Since you're not happy about it, you don't have to pray for him.

16:11.014 --> 16:12.035
He doesn't say that.

16:12.575 --> 16:24.026
He says, it doesn't matter what your opinion is about your life circumstances, pray for those around you who are in your community or where you are taking captive.

16:24.546 --> 16:25.247
Pray for him.

16:30.472 --> 16:36.818
You can grow, bloom, and produce fruit wherever you wind up.

16:40.194 --> 16:54.370
It's hard for me to explain in real terms how much of an impact the last year and a half have had on me about community and what it's all about.

16:55.371 --> 17:06.324
But I promise you that it's not lost on me that we together have done a whole lot of things that I never thought I would do or could do.

17:07.765 --> 17:08.466
And I think

17:09.058 --> 17:22.591
Because of that it gives me more confidence to take the risk that God asks us to take to do the things God asks us to do because I know it's not something far-fetched but because we do it together.

17:23.812 --> 17:27.175
It gives you confidence when you know there's people behind you.

17:29.377 --> 17:38.866
It's really difficult when you venture out and you don't have a home base that's safe or someone's saying, I'll be here to help you and encourage you along the way.

17:39.010 --> 17:50.589
It's really important to know that people got your back, that they're in your corner, that they're fighting for you, fighting with you, and helping you to do the things God wants you to do.

17:51.230 --> 17:54.616
I've had to learn that in new ways, from you all.

17:56.459 --> 17:58.021
It's been a wonderful experience.

17:58.041 --> 18:05.714
It's so humbling to me to see the change in my own perspective about community, about mission,

18:06.018 --> 18:09.962
about love, about what needs we need to meet and things like that.

18:10.763 --> 18:17.650
And I never would have anticipated that except for a community of believers who stand with me.

18:20.953 --> 18:22.235
You don't do this alone.

18:23.356 --> 18:24.457
God goes with you.

18:25.538 --> 18:28.761
It's not something where I got this big task and I don't know if I can do it.

18:29.322 --> 18:30.583
God called me to it.

18:30.603 --> 18:33.266
He's going to bring the people and resources to it.

18:34.978 --> 18:37.522
It amazes me how God does that.

18:39.104 --> 18:40.606
But He's so good at it.

18:44.993 --> 18:48.759
And when He puts you in a place, being rooted doesn't mean you stay stuck.

18:50.181 --> 18:51.823
It means you're being steady.

18:52.905 --> 18:57.091
So He told Israel, dig in, be steady in your presence.

18:57.592 --> 19:04.562
Learn again to be obedient to me in adverse situations so I know you really mean it.

19:04.898 --> 19:07.622
Because in your prosperity, you forgot me.

19:11.768 --> 19:13.551
In our prosperity, we forget God.

19:13.591 --> 19:16.636
He gives us adverse situations, so we don't forget Him.

19:16.976 --> 19:17.918
God, I need your help.

19:18.639 --> 19:19.801
When we get it, we go, thank you.

19:19.821 --> 19:20.702
God, I got it now.

19:21.904 --> 19:23.266
And that's not what He wants.

19:23.907 --> 19:26.371
He wants to say, OK, now you're restored.

19:26.952 --> 19:28.314
Now you're prosperous.

19:29.335 --> 19:33.842
Let's see what you can do to bless others with that, to keep growing.

19:33.922 --> 19:36.525
and building out what God has put in.

19:42.172 --> 20:01.714
In Psalm chapter 1 verse 3 it says, a person who, let me describe the context, if you trust in the Lord and His Word and you delight in it, it says this, the one who does that shall be like a tree planted by rivers of water that brings forth its fruit in its season.

20:03.586 --> 20:07.152
That's such a beautiful picture to me of community.

20:08.134 --> 20:24.581
That when you are deeply rooted in God's Word and delight in it, God's going to plant you at a place to continually feed your root system because you're rooted in it and now God's bringing the water to where the roots are.

20:25.923 --> 20:30.130
But at the same time, it's bringing forth fruit which goes out.

20:32.866 --> 20:34.368
I like that image.

20:38.074 --> 20:49.671
And so when we talk about community and a place where we live, there are some of us here who can say, I lived in this community my entire life.

20:51.734 --> 20:56.341
Some of us can say, this is my hometown.

20:57.843 --> 20:59.105
I was a pastor's kid.

20:59.626 --> 21:02.610
I went to college also and

21:02.690 --> 21:03.471
I moved a lot.

21:04.992 --> 21:08.696
So by the time I was 31, I had moved 31 times.

21:09.837 --> 21:12.099
A lot of that was transitioning in college years.

21:12.920 --> 21:18.825
But most of it was from one place to another and not to the same people.

21:19.886 --> 21:23.189
So when I was asked, what's your hometown?

21:24.430 --> 21:28.354
I would have to think about the place that I lived the longest.

21:28.374 --> 21:32.498
Because I said, well, a lot of my friends are from that town.

21:32.610 --> 21:36.895
But I live longer here, and that's where I went to grade school and middle school.

21:37.316 --> 21:38.597
So maybe that's it.

21:39.558 --> 21:41.301
And I would call that my hometown.

21:42.202 --> 21:54.176
But from the very young age till 2009, my parents had a home place in Pope County where they retired to that we would go to frequently.

21:54.256 --> 21:56.799
So then I thought, well, maybe that's my hometown.

21:57.380 --> 22:02.386
If you don't know where you're from and rooted at, people will say, how do you connect?

22:04.034 --> 22:05.876
So I had a lot of short-term friendships.

22:07.118 --> 22:17.551
So learning and having root in the same town at Paducah now for more than any place in my life, I like being rooted.

22:19.534 --> 22:22.838
I like having the same friends and the same people around.

22:23.198 --> 22:27.984
It's very comforting to me to know if there's something I need done, I know who I can call.

22:29.927 --> 22:32.530
In a new place, a new town, you don't know who

22:32.610 --> 22:38.899
like the record service or who you call for information about something, but when you live there a long time, you know.

22:39.680 --> 22:41.122
I like that knowing.

22:41.563 --> 22:43.365
That's what community does for you.

22:43.926 --> 22:48.112
It brings this sense of familiarity which doesn't breed contempt.

22:48.532 --> 22:53.359
It brings gratitude that you know who you can count on.

22:55.562 --> 22:57.585
And people know your character.

22:59.848 --> 23:01.170
If you're new to a community,

23:01.730 --> 23:03.938
And someone says something about you that's not true.

23:04.661 --> 23:06.006
Nobody's going to know if it's true or not.

23:06.949 --> 23:11.666
But if you're from there and you've got a reputation that's strong and solid, praise God.

23:23.074 --> 23:25.737
Why society is changing so rapidly?

23:25.777 --> 23:28.200
Are you searching for the reasons why?

