24:03.042 --> 24:09.652
One thing we learn about Jesus, and if you've ever done experiencing God, this may sound a little familiar.

24:10.373 --> 24:20.428
In John chapter 5 verse 17, Jesus says, my father has been working until now, and I have been working.

24:22.210 --> 24:25.756
Jesus didn't bring God into the city.

24:28.079 --> 24:32.786
He revealed God's activity that was already there.

24:33.826 --> 24:34.727
Think of it like this.

24:35.248 --> 24:42.459
He looked out across the fields and said to the disciples, the fields are ripe for harvest.

24:44.723 --> 24:45.764
He didn't get that ready.

24:46.626 --> 24:47.667
It was already ready.

24:49.029 --> 24:57.182
So God was doing something to make people ready to be harvest, to be a recipient of the good news.

24:58.424 --> 24:59.586
That's already there.

25:01.469 --> 25:02.450
All we have to do

25:02.658 --> 25:08.567
is be at the right place with the right mindset at the right time and people will receive it.

25:12.513 --> 25:20.285
And those deeds become opportunities and strangers become partners in ministry or otherwise.

25:20.865 --> 25:26.514
And a change in the community around us and influx becomes an opportunity for invitation.

25:31.938 --> 25:36.002
The problem is we can get bogged down in how we're used to seeing things in people.

25:38.164 --> 25:50.736
If you know what I mean by that, it means sometimes we think apple doesn't fall far from the tree, leopard can't change his spots, but I want to tell you something.

25:50.756 --> 25:52.497
God delights in doing the impossible.

25:52.998 --> 26:01.746
He likes showing people the transformation can make in a life that's totally been destroyed to bring a total place of light and salvation.

26:02.562 --> 26:05.546
There is no such thing for God as someone unredeemable.

26:07.248 --> 26:11.214
There is no person that God can't transform.

26:13.917 --> 26:20.266
I know a man who had a reputation because he earned it.

26:21.307 --> 26:21.808
A bad one.

26:23.110 --> 26:24.892
And I invited him to church.

26:26.154 --> 26:27.255
He had never been to church.

26:28.297 --> 26:29.358
He didn't know anything about it.

26:30.119 --> 26:32.402
So we're greeting each other in the church.

26:32.674 --> 26:34.877
And he drops a swear word.

26:36.941 --> 26:38.783
And now he's from that community, right?

26:38.843 --> 26:44.031
So they know his reputation, his story, and they look at it and they go, oh, he just said that word.

26:44.532 --> 26:45.454
Oh, he said that word.

26:45.534 --> 26:46.155
Oh, no, no, no.

26:46.695 --> 26:48.879
And I, and he didn't talk to him about it.

26:48.939 --> 26:52.985
They just said, well, I'll tell you that guy is just as bad as his brother.

26:53.626 --> 27:01.458
So what they said, and I went up to him later privately and I said, listen, in church, I know you never been.

27:01.922 --> 27:07.851
but we drop the four letter words, we come to try to praise God and talk about God.

27:08.612 --> 27:11.416
And God isn't a four letter word descriptor.

27:13.019 --> 27:17.125
But he was talking about praising God, but he threw his swear word in there.

27:17.706 --> 27:20.911
It was the most bizarre thing I've ever experienced.

27:21.992 --> 27:24.997
It was like good bad at the same time.

27:25.057 --> 27:28.041
And so after that he said, thank you.

27:28.702 --> 27:29.143
I didn't know.

27:29.183 --> 27:31.186
I'll work on that.

27:31.458 --> 27:34.882
You see, when God changes you, He changes your language and what you talk about.

27:35.763 --> 27:37.545
And this is God working on this guy.

27:39.368 --> 27:42.832
Nobody else talked to him about it.

27:43.953 --> 27:45.796
They might have said, you ain't supposed to do that.

27:45.856 --> 27:46.637
What's wrong with you?

27:47.397 --> 27:53.725
But they didn't say, hey, let's come alongside you and disciple you and show you how I live out of Christian life.

27:54.626 --> 27:55.287
I did that.

27:56.228 --> 28:00.914
And he was so appreciative of how I talked with him and treated him

28:01.186 --> 28:02.928
that he called me his best friend.

28:07.795 --> 28:17.649
Because I cared, the mission opportunity was right in front of me, and I didn't have the preconceived notions that he was going to stay at the same.

28:22.616 --> 28:29.426
And what's funny, over time, people's perceptions change of who he was.

28:30.722 --> 28:32.645
He became chair of the PPRC.

28:33.626 --> 28:35.408
He became involved in the trustees.

28:35.448 --> 28:39.373
He became involved in the ministries of the church and expanding the ministries.

28:39.934 --> 28:46.723
And on the day when he lost his life, people said, well, we can do without him.

28:48.946 --> 28:54.473
From, oh, he just don't need to be here talking like that to, well, we can do without him.

28:54.994 --> 28:55.795
That's God.

28:56.476 --> 28:57.938
That's what community does.

28:58.178 --> 29:03.504
We get transformed by God in community by people who reflect the love of God to us.

29:10.712 --> 29:17.460
We must move from being a church that meets in the community to a church that moves through the community.

29:18.040 --> 29:24.388
So throughout our days and people we interact with, we're not just a Sunday person.

29:25.088 --> 29:26.610
We also live for God.

29:27.170 --> 29:30.795
and try to disciple every day of the week wherever we found.

29:32.437 --> 29:33.739
I think that makes sense.

29:34.580 --> 29:46.096
Whether it's a workplace, formal workplace, a school, cafe conversations, whatever, wherever you find yourself, those can be sacred routes.

29:47.478 --> 29:50.582
Because you're a regular routine, people know you there.

29:52.405 --> 29:56.050
And the people who know you are the ones who trust you more than those who don't.

30:00.418 --> 30:04.904
And this church and the people here make excellent inroads into the community.

30:05.865 --> 30:06.346
Excellent.

30:07.468 --> 30:08.489
But we can still do better.

30:08.529 --> 30:13.496
And God asks us to continue to be intentional about it.

30:16.280 --> 30:23.589
God gives us roots to stay nourished, but the routes of our lives to stay missional in our focus.

30:26.774 --> 30:29.938
In Acts chapter 8 it says, the believers who were scattered

30:30.562 --> 30:33.386
preached the good news wherever they went.

30:34.568 --> 30:37.613
That means wherever we go is an opportunity.

30:38.494 --> 30:44.223
Every road leading from our church is a route of potential redemption for somebody.

30:46.326 --> 30:48.109
Doesn't matter what direction that road goes.

30:49.431 --> 30:51.114
In other words, we don't have to pick and choose.

30:53.337 --> 30:56.562
Each person needs salvation

30:56.866 --> 31:00.912
And each person at one point in their life or another needs hope or encouragement.

31:04.017 --> 31:04.958
Somewhere along the way.

31:05.959 --> 31:10.726
And if we don't know them, don't have interaction with them, we're not going to know what they need.

31:15.413 --> 31:20.301
So before we can speak into the community, we must serve it first.

31:20.982 --> 31:23.986
That's what I think is so great about our senior dinners.

31:24.258 --> 31:53.970
the Halloween things we do and several other ministries that were involved in we're serving into our community and I believe the community knows who we are and When they think of Palestine United Methodist Church, they think I love that church I Know that church and it's a good Comment that people say if you look at it like this a Good reputation is priceless

31:54.818 --> 31:59.144
a bad reputation will follow you even in transformation.

32:00.946 --> 32:07.215
And this church has an excellent reputation for loving, serving, and get this.

32:07.235 --> 32:07.856
Y'all know this.

32:08.497 --> 32:08.978
Community.

32:10.440 --> 32:12.042
We're all about our community.

32:12.643 --> 32:13.945
That's important to us.

32:14.385 --> 32:15.767
And people know that.

32:16.728 --> 32:19.452
And it's okay to say, we love our community.

32:19.512 --> 32:20.614
I put it on the church sign.

32:20.934 --> 32:21.916
We love our community.

32:22.216 --> 32:23.698
You are our community.

32:25.058 --> 32:27.301
Whoever you is, they are our community.

32:27.841 --> 32:30.725
Whoever passes by that sign, that's our community.

32:32.026 --> 32:33.108
And I think we know that.

32:33.608 --> 32:38.174
And I'm so thankful that I don't have to say, you know, anybody around here should be your community.

32:38.354 --> 32:39.075
You already know.

32:39.095 --> 32:41.538
I don't have to convince you of that.

32:42.839 --> 32:43.580
Thank God.

32:43.620 --> 32:48.005
I don't have to convince you of that because this will take a long time to learn.

32:51.109 --> 32:51.890
So when we

32:52.354 --> 32:53.175
Seek community.

32:53.195 --> 33:00.544
What we're seeking is its peace or its Shalom in Jeremiah 29 7 where it says pray for the peace of the community.

33:02.286 --> 33:06.611
When we see that word peace in that verse, the word is actually Shalom.

33:08.093 --> 33:17.264
Shalom is a word that means wholeness, harmony, rightness, and it's all based in God.

33:18.165 --> 33:19.186
And so when the church

33:19.650 --> 33:31.368
pursues shalom for the community, and we as individuals do, it becomes a prophetic presence, not just preaching salvation, but demonstrating it.

33:33.972 --> 33:47.794
Now when I say prophetic presence, what I mean by that is that when the word is spoken, it isn't necessarily a future-oriented end times, prophecy word like that.

33:48.322 --> 34:00.295
Any time the word of God is shared that gives an impactful message, whether it's for right now, for an encouragement, for healing, restoration, all Scripture is prophetic.

34:01.036 --> 34:07.803
And what that means is it's what God is trying to tell you right now.

34:10.185 --> 34:14.610
And I pray that each time I speak that I've got a

34:15.170 --> 34:18.934
a thumb on the pulse of God and what he's trying to tell us right now.

34:21.237 --> 34:25.282
So a prophetic word can be a teaching word, encouraging word.

34:25.843 --> 34:26.884
It can be challenging.

34:27.405 --> 34:42.162
It can be a it can be a future oriented word or this is what God wants you to do type word but it doesn't have to be but the message is one of those moments where God can meet you and where you are

34:42.242 --> 34:43.683
and speak into your life.

34:43.723 --> 34:44.765
That's a prophetic word.

34:44.805 --> 34:45.465
It's all it is.

34:48.128 --> 34:48.909
I think that's good.

34:52.873 --> 35:00.340
So we know community and we know prophetic word and we know that it's valuable.

35:02.502 --> 35:03.203
So what's next?

35:04.084 --> 35:08.909
How do we put the rubber to the road, the shoulder to the grindstone?

35:09.049 --> 35:09.970
What can we do?

35:10.626 --> 35:39.442
And there's some very simple things that you are probably already doing some of them But you can do it more intentionally and one of them is to pray for our community To pray for them to pray for their peace to pray for their prosperity to pray also that they know who God is That's quite simple and then we can learn the local rhythms and events that are around and be involved in community events even in

35:39.554 --> 35:50.324
ones we don't necessarily want to go to because if people see you consistently at those events, they're going to want to connect and associate with you and then you have opportunity for conversation.

35:51.505 --> 35:56.070
And conversation is exactly how you talk about what matters.

35:57.751 --> 36:07.821
I never saw Jesus in scripture anywhere except on the cross, not speak the message.

36:07.841 --> 36:09.362
He always spoke the message.

36:09.634 --> 36:11.997
So we had to have a way to do that.

36:14.700 --> 36:18.644
We can partner with other folks who are doing stuff that we want to do.

36:19.846 --> 36:24.311
If another organization or a church is doing something, we say, we want to help you.

36:25.933 --> 36:28.956
And we feel like God is asking us to do something.

36:28.976 --> 36:31.039
Then when we go to them and say, hey, would you help us?

36:31.800 --> 36:37.266
They'd say yes, because they know we're in it for the kingdom, not for just us.

36:39.938 --> 36:43.403
so we can line up with people who are doing good.

36:47.429 --> 36:58.206
We can celebrate the things that are impacting that are God-breathed stuff from our area around us.

36:58.927 --> 37:03.714
If someone that we know receives salvation, it's great for the whole community to hear about it.

37:04.115 --> 37:08.882
If someone gets a miracle like Donald, it's great for the whole, we all rejoice together.

37:09.090 --> 37:09.931
That's community.

37:15.478 --> 37:19.824
We are limited only by our willingness to do what it takes.

37:20.384 --> 37:20.945
And that's it.

37:22.607 --> 37:24.930
Got a short story to close with.

37:25.311 --> 37:26.632
I think you'll appreciate this.

37:30.637 --> 37:32.920
She was 84 years old.

37:35.403 --> 37:37.426
I remember church I was passoring.

37:38.530 --> 37:46.042
And she and her friend, Ms. Thomas, you don't know any of them, they're not from around here and they're all deceased many years ago.

37:46.082 --> 37:50.368
And she and Ms. Thomas went together and did everything everywhere.

37:50.729 --> 37:57.699
One came to my church with the methods, Ms. Thomas went to another Methodist church and sometimes a Baptist church.

37:58.501 --> 38:07.154
And they did everything together and one day they got mad and they were angry at each other and they stopped talking.

38:07.554 --> 38:12.741
My eight-year-old four-year-old friend said, yeah, she's not coming here anymore for Bible study or anything.

38:14.083 --> 38:15.605
We're just not talking to each other.

38:15.625 --> 38:18.269
And I said, well, what do you do about that?

38:18.409 --> 38:22.335
She said, well, until she does something I can't because she don't want to talk to me.

38:23.917 --> 38:27.482
And so try and find something you can do to open the door for that conversation.

38:29.845 --> 38:30.406
So get this.

38:31.488 --> 38:35.954
She goes home, thinks about it a while, grabs a plate, serving plate,

38:36.258 --> 38:49.212
Bakes some cookies, puts it on the plate, goes next door, which is where the lady lived, knots on her door, she opens it, the lady won't say where she hands her to play the cookies.

38:50.394 --> 38:51.555
Goes back home.

38:52.376 --> 38:54.999
The next day, they knock on her door.

38:56.140 --> 38:58.603
Same plate, fresh bags of cookies.

38:59.924 --> 39:03.408
They started talking.

39:03.428 --> 39:05.170
And she said, why?

39:07.490 --> 39:15.599
did you make me cookies and bring them to me when I made a bash for you?

39:16.079 --> 39:20.204
She said, well, I ate them and I couldn't return your plate empty.

39:23.107 --> 39:26.831
Hear this, and odds, not getting along.

39:27.492 --> 39:29.213
And there was an act of kindness.

39:30.655 --> 39:35.180
And the other one said, that must be an olive branch or something.

39:36.461 --> 39:37.202
And she brought

39:37.314 --> 39:38.035
a plate back.

39:38.335 --> 39:41.779
And she said, you know, that's what the conversation they have.

39:41.799 --> 39:43.661
And I said, you know, that's amazing.

39:43.681 --> 39:44.162
We did that.

39:44.582 --> 39:46.724
There's some people who are strange from our church.

39:46.764 --> 39:48.166
Maybe we can give them a plate of cookies.

39:49.347 --> 39:53.852
They started getting plates of cookies and saying, here's a plate of cookie for you.

39:53.872 --> 39:56.295
Just want to know you were thinking about it.

39:56.315 --> 40:01.801
Invariably, those folks sent a full plate of cookies back.

40:02.722 --> 40:06.226
This became the ministry and 84 year old woman did.

40:07.074 --> 40:08.015
She started it.

40:08.036 --> 40:10.219
That's community.

40:10.740 --> 40:11.261
That's it.

40:11.441 --> 40:12.322
I'm reaching out.

40:12.823 --> 40:16.048
And I only had to say anything because she wouldn't talk to her anyway.

40:17.610 --> 40:18.632
Just say, here you go.

40:21.156 --> 40:22.558
That's what community is about.

40:22.799 --> 40:25.383
And I believe we are able to do that.

40:26.665 --> 40:28.027
So I leave you with this question.

40:30.751 --> 40:35.218
If somebody's in your path, can you trust that God put them there for a purpose, for a reason?

40:36.258 --> 40:38.000
And can you just do that?

40:40.843 --> 40:53.437
Can you think like that this week that maybe this person's right in my path, not because they're there randomly, because maybe God wants me to step out of my comfort zone and love them.

40:56.000 --> 40:56.780
Would you pray with me?

40:58.502 --> 41:02.667
Heavenly Father, thank you for the opportunities you provide.

41:03.348 --> 41:05.650
Help us to be community minded the way

41:06.114 --> 41:33.170
Community is supposed to be not the way it used to be presented But people loving and encouraging each other that's transformation and I know we each wouldn't hear have a heart for that so help us to See what you're doing Lord to hear it and share with one another the good The good work you want to do the good work you are doing We may bless encourage and resource

41:34.754 --> 41:39.143
And Lord, you might change the world around us that we would have an impact for you.

41:41.128 --> 41:42.751
I pray this in your precious son's name.

41:43.272 --> 41:53.574
Amen.

